Find the area of each rectangle.    

[[☃ image 1]]

$\begin{align}
\underbrace{\blueE{\text{Area}}}_{\text{large rectangle }} &= {7} \times {6}\\\\
&= \blueE{42 \text{ square cm}}
\end{align}$

[[☃ image 2]]

$\begin{align}
\underbrace{\maroonE{\text{Area}}}_{\text{small rectangle }} &= {3} \times {3}\\\\
&= \maroonE{9 \text{ square cm}}
\end{align}$

$\begin{align}
\underbrace{\purpleD{\text{Area}}}_{\text{shaded figure }}&=\underbrace{\blueE{\text{Area}}}_{\text{large rectangle }}-\underbrace{\maroonE{\text{Area}}}_{\text{small rectangle }}\\\\
&=\blueE{42 \text{ square cm}} - \maroonE{9 \text{ square cm}}\\\\
&= \purpleD{33\text{ square cm}}
\end{align}$
